23/03/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A Croatian Serb national with UK citizenship was arrested in Belgrade on suspicions of involvement in the 1991 Ovcara farm massacre, the Serbian war crimes prosecution announced on Saturday (March 22nd). Milorad Pejic is suspected of being a member of the Vukovar Territorial Defence at the time. Around 200 Croatian prisoners were murdered at the farm after being taken there from a local hospital. Pejic, who lived in the United Kingdom, was arrested at the Nikola Tesla airport in Belgrade on March 19th based on an international warrant. (Hina, Vecernji List, Reuters, AFP, Tanjug, B92 - 22/03/08) 
